Anniversary of DPRK-Russia Joint Declaration Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 19 (KCNA) -- Russian President V.V. Putin visited the DPRK from July 19 to 20, 2000 at the invitation of leader Kim Jong Il. Putin was the first head of state of Russia to visit the DPRK. The DPRK-Russia Joint Declaration was adopted during the visit.
 Pyongyang-based newspapers today dedicate articles to this anniversary. The articles say that the adoption of the joint declaration was an important event as it provided a solid basis for developing in depth the DPRK-Russia relations of friendship and cooperation on a new track as required by the new century. Over the last five years these relations have steadily developed on a new stage under the special care of the top leaders of the two countries, they added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun recalls that Kim Jong Il visited Russia twice, recording a brilliant page in the history of DPRK-Russia friendship and greatly contributing to the strengthening of the bilateral friendship and peace and security in Asia and the rest of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years the DPRK-Russia relations have become closer in various fields on the basis of the joint declarations, the paper notes, and says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the Russian people are working hard to achieve social stability and national unity and defend the security and interests of the country under the leadership of Putin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian leadership set a general goal to build a strong state and is guiding the people to its attainment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Russia's say and prestige are rising in the international arena. Its efforts to defend global peace and security and establish a sound international relationship have been supported worldwide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people appreciate the Russian government and people's efforts for social development and national security and interests and sincerely hope that everything will go well in Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that the Korean people will strive to boost the bilateral relations of friendship and cooperation in the spirit of the DPRK-Russia Joint Declaration.

Japan's Wild Ambition for Military Supremacy Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 19 (KCNA) -- Japan has recently announced the "2005 defence white paper" in which it cited the so-called "military threat" from the DPRK and China and vociferated about the importance of increasing the military muscle to cope with it and escalating the military actions to ensure maritime security.
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed commentary observes this move is a revelation of Japan's sinister aim to justify its ambition for emerging a military giant and its moves for reinvasion and thus hold military supremacy in the Asian region under the pretext of coping with the "military threat" from the DPRK and China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By adding even "military threat" from China to the one from the DPRK, Japan seeks to create impression at home and abroad that its security is exposed to a bigger threat than before and thus legally step up in real earnest its moves for turning itself into a military giant and launching reinvasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese militarists listed the DPRK and China as its principal enemies and are now working hard to seize Korea, to begin with, and, using it as a springboard, invade China to conquer the rest of Asia as they did in the past. 
 The Japanese reactionaries are sparking off territorial disputes, deliberately insisting that Tok Islet, an inseparable part of the territory of Korea, and Diaoyu islands of China belong to the territory of Japan. This is nothing but a deliberate premeditated move to strain the situation in the region and create an environment favorable for becoming a military giant and realizing its wild ambition for reinvasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries and the U.S. agreed to boost the military alliance and make a common use of the military bases of the "Self-Defence Forces" and the U.S. troops. This is part of their military preparations for reinvasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK are following the moves of the Japanese reactionaries for reinvasion with high vigilance. If the Japanese reactionaries dare encroach upon the sovereignty of the DPRK even a bit, the army and people of the DPRK will not miss the opportunity to give vent to the pent-up grudge against the sworn enemy but mete out merciless punishment to them.

Fuller Play to Heroic Stamina of Songun Korea Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 19 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Tuesday devotes a page to an editorial article titled �gThe general march of the Songun revolution is a heroic one in our times.�h
 The general march of the Songun revolution is a successful continuation of the proud history and tradition of the Korean revolution which has demonstrated only victory through heroic marches and its development in depth at a new higher stage, the article notes, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the on-going drive of our army and people that decides the steady victory in our revolution or its failure. It is the only way of winning one victory after another and paving the wide avenue for bringing about the greatest national prosperity to conduct a more dynamic all-people march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The essential characteristic feature and might of the general march lie in that the People's Army, invincible revolutionary armed forces, is projected as a main force and the revolutionary soldier spirit and heroic fighting traits created by it serve as a powerful engine and the perfect unity of the army and people in thinking and fighting traits gives strong impetus to the advance of the times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general march is the most powerful all-people grand march in history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For our army and people the general march serves as a sacred struggle in which they share their destiny with their leader to the last and work hard to bring about the prosperity of the country and happiness of all generations to come, true to the cause of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general march is an all-people one to devotedly defend the headquarters of the revolution and an offensive for protecting the socialist country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Final victory in the present confrontation with the U.S. and success in building a great prosperous powerful nation lie in devotedly defending the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The outstanding leadership provided by the headquarters of the revolution is a sure guarantee for the victorious general march. The wise leadership provided by Kim Jong Il over the general march imbues our army and people with immense confidence and optimism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The invincible military power and single-minded unity are the driving force of the general march. They are the master key to achieving leaping advance of the country and its prosperity despite the enemies' obstinate offensive to isolate and stifle the DPRK and destabilize it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK's army and single-minded unity that have grown strong by dint of the great Songun political mode serve as the most powerful weapon in the general march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The victory in the general march is guaranteed by the Korean-style line of economic construction and the tremendous potential of the independent economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ideology is the most powerful weapon for the general march and the Songun revolution advances and emerges victorious thanks to its might. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the primary task of the general march to consolidate the politico-ideological position of socialism as firm as a rock by conducting the ideological work in a dynamic and unique manner. It is necessary to concentrate efforts on the ideological work for preparing the servicepersons of the People's Army and members of the Party and other working people as genuine Songun revolutionary soldiers who, armed with the spirit of devotedly defending the headquarters of the revolution, have made the Juche idea, the Songun idea, their faith. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is important to deepen the ideological education aimed at instilling the faith and optimism about socialism into them in combination with the work for establishing a socialist view on morality and the lifestyle based on collectivism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underscoring the need to give full play to the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance in the general march, the article stresses that one should believe in one's own strength and self-reliance is the only way to live. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Party members, servicepersons and people should come out as one to thoroughly implement the joint slogans of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the WPK and thus fully demonstrate the might of the Songun unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article calls upon everyone to single-mindedly unite around Kim Jong Il and demonstrate to the full the heroic spirit of Songun Korea in the general march.

Lectures on Anniversary of Kwangju Popular Uprising Given in U.S. and Canada 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 19 (KCNA) -- A group of lecturers of the Nationwide Special Committee for Probing the Truth behind the GIs' Massacres recently toured 19 cities including Washington, New York, Atlanta, Chicago, San Francisco and Los Angeles of the U.S. and Toronto of Canada to give lectures on the occasion of the 25th anniversary of the Kwangju Popular Uprising.
 Present there were compatriots organizations in the U.S. and Canada including the U.S. Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification, the Federation of Koreans in the U.S., the Canadian Regional Headquarters of the nationwide special committee, the Hangyore Federation of Koreans in the U.S., the Minjok Thongsin and the People for Building the Future, and Koreans there, the International Action Centre and the peace movement organizations in the U.S. and anti-war peace champions, activists and youth and students and citizens from different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hyo Sok, co-representative of the Kwangju-South Jolla Provincial Headquarters of the nationwide special committee, who participated in the uprising and Ri Sin, head of the investigation group of the headquarters, who is one of the witnesses of the uprising gave lectures in which they disclosed the thrice-cursed monstrous crimes the military fascist clique of south Korea committed by suppressing the just struggle of the Kwangju resistance fighters in cold blood after branding them as mobs and the true colors of the U.S. as back-stage wirepuller of their massacre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Strongly lashing out at the U.S. for pursuing a hostile policy towards the DPRK and working hard to unleash a nuclear war against it, they held that the short-cut to defusing the tension on the Korean Peninsula is for the DPRK and the U.S. to conclude a peace agreement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Persons of conscience and anti-war peace champions in the U.S. and American witnesses of the Kwangju massacre in their speeches strongly demanded the pullback of the U.S. forces from south Korea, the withdrawal of the U.S. hostile policy towards the DPRK, the conclusion of the DPRK-U.S. peace agreement and a halt to the threat of war against the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Video tape titled "May Comes Again" was shown during the lectures.

Poems and Words of Song Praising Kim Jong Il Created by Russians 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 19 (KCNA) -- Russian poets Aleksandr Konstantsinovich Rabchev and Oleg Naumov created poems and words of a song in high praises of leader Kim Jong Il.
 Aleksandr in his poem "Appearance of Great Sun" praised Kim Jong Il as a great sun of the new century who paved an eternal way for the DPRK-Russia friendship to follow and indicated a rosy future of the era of independence, adding that it was the greatest honor of Russia that Lake Baikal was honored with the appearance of the great sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He in the words of a song "Songun Brilliant Commander of the World" sang in high praises of Kim Jong Il as the Songun brilliant commander of the world who unrolled the Songun policy to defend peace and the red flag of socialism with arms under the uplifted revolutionary banner at the juncture when the people stood at the crossroads of war or peace, socialism or imperialism and revolution or surrender. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Oleg in his poems "Songun Brilliant Commander", "Socialism Is Sure to Triumph" and "May the DPRK Eternally Prosper" said that Korean socialism was sure to triumph, adding that socialism was defended and people were united single-mindedly as brothers as Kim Jong Il, Songun brilliant commander, paved a wide avenue of Songun and rallied them with one ideology and led them to victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Songun means an eternal victory and Korea holding Kim Jong Il, Songun brilliant commander, in high esteem will eternally prosper.

Inter-Korean Students' Meeting Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mt. Kumgang resort, July 18 (KCNA) -- A meeting of students in the north and the south of Korea for implementing the June 15 joint declaration and realizing national cooperation for peace against war was held at Mt. Kumgang resort on July 17 and 18.
 Present there were the delegation of the Korean Student Committee and the south side's delegation grouping the central and regional representatives of the student movement headquarters for implementing the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Sung Chol, vice-chairman of the Korean Student Committee, in his opening address said that the epochal events in the development of the inter-Korean ties and the national reunification movement and the meeting of students in the north and the south are a great fruition provided in the era when the June 15 joint declaration was published. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called on the students in the north and the south to widely introduce the vitality and validity of the joint declaration to the popular masses and launch a vigorous action to realize the three forms of cooperation for national independence, peace against war and reunification and patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed belief that through the current meeting, the students in the north and the south would pool their will and efforts to deepen and strengthen their trust and cohesion and realize the three forms of cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Congratulatory messages from different bodies in the north and the south were introduced and a resolution forum of students in the north and the south was held at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers at the forum said that true patriotism and the way to reunification at present is to closely unite under the banner of the June 15 joint declaration. And they called upon the youth and students in the north and the south to pool efforts and wisdom of the youth and become a model of national unity in the patriotic reunification movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A joint resolution of the students in the north and the south of Korea for implementing the national reunification declaration was adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Jae Yong, representative of the south side, in his closing address stated that thanks to the joint declaration the unity in the idea of "By our nation itself" has been further strengthened over the last five years and the era of independent reunification, the era of reconciliation and cooperation, was opened. And he called on the students in the north and the south to become the vanguard for the reunification movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the meeting, students from the north and the south gave an art performance showing the will of the 70 million Koreans desirous of national independent reunification and the stamina and optimism of the youth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants had a joint mountaineering around Samil Lagoon.

Optical Fiber Communication Cables Connected for TV Dialog between Separated Families and Relatives 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kaesong, July 18 (KCNA) -- Optical fiber communication cables for TV dialog between separated families and relatives in the north and the south of Korea were connected under an agreement reached at the 15th inter-Korean ministerial talks and the inter-Korean working-level Red-Cross contact.
 A ceremony of connecting the cable links took place in the Demilitarized Zone of the Military Demarcation Line on July 18. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were persons concerned including communication personnel in the north and the south of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the cable links between Kaesong and Munsan was connected. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The connection of the cable links in the idea of "By our nation itself" has made it possible to successfully realize the TV dialog between separated families and relatives in the north and the south of Korea on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of Korea's liberation and contribute to the reconciliation, unity, cooperation and reunification of the nation.

Abe's Militarist Remarks Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 19 (KCNA) -- Abe, acting secretary general of the Liberal Democratic Party of Japan, in a lecture in Osaka on July 3 let loose a string of balderdash that the prime minister prayed for the souls of the fallen fighters at the "Yasukuni Shrine" and this is a universally accepted common sense. In May when Abe visited the United States he asserted that the next prime minister, too, should visit the shrine because it is the responsibility and duty of the chief executive to express respects to those who fought for the country.
 In this regard Minju Joson today says in a signed commentary: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Judging from the fact that Abe is strongly assertive for Japanese rulers' visit to the shrine, it is clear that he wishes to become the second Tojo and see his name to go down to posterity. That is why he does not hesitate to drive Japan to its second defeat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sophism about "universally accepted common sense" and reckless remarks about "the fallen fighters" made by him in a bid to justify the prime minister's visit to the shrine clearly suggest his sinister political intention. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The ulterior aim of Abe is to provide a justification for visits to the shrine by state leaders by painting as "fallen fighters" the war criminals who were sternly punished by history as the enemies of international justice and human conscience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He is covetous of the post of the next prime minister. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not hard to guess what will be the future of Japan in case the power is seized by such political mountebank who does not hesitate to lead the country to self-destruction in quest of "honor" good-for-nothing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military fanatics are bound to go to ruin.

Koreans Called upon to Turn Out for Building Reunified Powerful Nation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 19 (KCNA) -- The joint slogans of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea released on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the WPK include the slogan "Let us build on the land of three thousand-ri a powerful nation, independent, prosperous and reunified!"
 Noting that the joint slogans earnestly called upon all the fellow countrymen to turn out to build a reunified powerful country, reflecting the unanimous aspiration, demand and will of the Koreans, Rodong Sinmun Tuesday says in a signed article: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint slogans calling for building a powerful nation, independent, prosperous and reunified, reflect the Juche-oriented idea, line and plan of the WPK for national reunification and serve as a banner giving strong spurs to the development of the times as they are in full accord with the trend and demand of the era of independent reunification and fully reflect them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The inter-Korean relations have turned into those guided by the spirit of "By our nation itself" and the movement for reconciliation and cooperation and independent reunification has made dynamic progress in the era of independent reunification. As a result, the Koreans have become stronger in their awareness of independence and inspiring successes have been made in the work for the common interests and prosperity of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is important is for the Korean nation to remain true to its great goal of independence and prosperity for all its members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If they invariably hold fast to the idea of "By our nation itself" to promote the common interests and prosperity of the nation through national reconciliation and cooperation and thus further develop the struggle to achieve independent reunification, a powerful country, independent, prosperous and reunified, will appear on this land as desired by all the fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint slogans lay down right and realistic tasks and targets of struggle as they correctly reflect the spirit and strong trend of the era of independent reunification and entirely conform with them. Precisely for this reason, the joint slogans not only powerfully encourage all the Koreans in the efforts to build a reunified powerful nation but put strong impetus to the development of the June 15 era of reunification with extraordinary attraction.

Efficient Farm Machines Introduced in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 19 (KCNA) -- The Institute of Agricultural Mechanization under the Academy of Agricultural Science of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has invented and introduced various kinds of efficient machines in farming.
 Typical of them is a mobile universal thrasher. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The machine can thrash rice, wheat, barley and bean, 1.5-2.5 tons per hour, with the power of an electric motor or tractor engine. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is trailed by a tractor to be installed in any place. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The institute has also made a harvester combine and a maize thrasher. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The former can be applied to the harvest of such crops as rice, wheat, barley, maize and kaoliang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The maize thrasher is small and light. And its electric consumption is 2.8 KW and capability 2 tons per hour.

Success in Research to Prevent Sea Disaster
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 19 (KCNA) -- Teachers and researchers of the Global Environmental Science Faculty of Kim Il Sung University have made successes in their research to prevent sea disasters.
 They, on the basis of a scientific analysis of oceanographic materials concerning several hundred points on the east and west coast of the country, have established a new tsunami warning system. The system timely and correctly forecast tsunami epicenter, time, speed and direction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In case a seaquake occurs in any place, it also indicates in detail the size of tsunami, the time it would take to the shore, damage it may cause to the coastal areas and measures to prevent casualties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Typical of their research successes is "Atlas for Forecasting Tsunamis in the East Sea of Korea". It thus helps prevent possible tsunami damage on the east coast. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the course of reproducing and analyzing with computer scores of tsunamis that have been recorded in the East Sea of Korea, they have found out the highest tidal waves which may be seen in the coming 10,000 years and calculated the highest water level of the sea caused by the global warming in the coming 100 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The research successes are helpful towards making a plan for land development and deciding on the height and durability of foundations of coastal structures including breakwater against tsunami.

Supreme Commander of KPA Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Unit
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 19 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, inspected KPA Unit 937 honored with the title of Kum Song Lifeguard situated on the forefront.
 After receiving a salute, he acquainted himself with the unit's performance of duty and its training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks to be fulfilled to increase the unit's combat capability in every way, satisfied to learn that the servicepersons of the unit have converted all the operational theatres into invulnerable fortresses with intense loyalty to the Party and the revolution and ardent patriotism and have been fully prepared as a-match-for-a hundred fighters capable of wiping out any formidable enemy at a single stroke. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He praised the servicepersons of the unit for performing their combat duties in a responsible manner with a high degree of vigilance, noting that the socialist motherland is sure to triumph as the forefront is guarded by the soldiers whose hearts are burning with the pledge to traverse with loyalty the road of the revolution to the last. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He dropped in at the servicepersons' hall where he learned about how the political and ideological work is conducted among the servicepersons, seeing entertainment facilities and visual aids. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted with appreciation that the unit is operating the servicepersons' hall on a regular basis after successfully building it into a centre for entertainment and conducting the revolutionary education, the working class education to suit the characteristic feature of the servicepersons. He underscored the need for the unit to pay primary attention to the ideological education to prepare all of them as soldiers equipped with the indomitable revolutionary spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he familiarized himself with the living of the servicepersons, looking round facilities for supplying service. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He called for directing sustained great efforts to the sideline farming to make the diet of the soldiers more affluent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Ri Yong Chol, member of the Central Military Commission of the WPK and first vice department director of its Central Committee, and Hwang Pyong So, vice department director of its Central Committee.

Spokesman for DPRK FM Dismisses Sheer Lie Spread by Some Unsavory Forces
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 19 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry Tuesday gave the following answer to the question put by KCNA refuting the sheer lie that a deputy to the Supreme People's Assembly allegedly working in the field of the munitions industry sought an "asylum" in south Korea, the fiction floated by some media of the U.S. and south Korea:
 The fiction is a sheer fabrication as there is no such institution in the north as the "marine industrial institute" to which he allegedly belonged. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "statement" allegedly made by him was full of lies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Some unsavory forces fabricated "the issue of a renegade-deserter," a fiction, in a bid to mislead the public opinion. This is, however, nothing but a despicable and ridiculous plot to tarnish the image of the dignified DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK cannot but maintain high vigilance and draw attention to the fact that the hostile forces are getting frantic in their false propaganda against it at a time when the north-south relations are making positive progress and the resumption of the six-party talks for the solution to the nuclear issue is near at hand.
